MAJOR DEVELOPMENTS (Always - 2-5 bullets)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

SCOPE: Company-specific announcements, strategic actions, material events disclosed in release
Logic: Material events that occurred or were announced - "what happened" this quarter

TEMPORAL GUIDANCE: Typically backward-looking (completed/announced events)
- Completed acquisitions, regulatory approvals received, contracts signed
- Announcements of future initiatives should focus on the announcement itself
- If initiative spans multiple quarters, consider also including in Strategic Initiatives

Include:
- M&A: Acquisitions, divestitures, partnerships (with amounts and timing)
- Leadership changes: VP level and above
- Regulatory: Investigations, litigation updates, approvals
- Major contracts: Customer/supply agreements (with amounts if disclosed)
- Strategic initiatives: New products, market entries, operational changes
- Capital allocation: Buyback authorizations, dividend changes, major capex programs

Format:
{
  "bullet_id": "aws_contract_expansion",
  "topic_label": "AWS Contract Expansion",
