Logic: Deep dive on transaction terms - the "HOW" that provides more detail than Major Developments

This section captures the "HOW" of transactions announced in Major Developments.
Extract specific terms disclosed in the filing.

Include all material terms provided - different transaction types will have
different relevant details:

- M&A Transactions: Consideration, earnouts, adjustments, closing conditions, protections
- Debt Instruments: Principal, rate, maturity, covenants, security, use of proceeds
- Equity Offerings: Shares, price, proceeds, underwriter terms, lock-ups
- Credit Facilities: Size, tranches, rates, covenants, security, fees
- Asset Transactions: Price, liabilities, adjustments, leaseback terms
- Joint Ventures: Ownership, contributions, governance, exit rights
- Restructuring: Exchange ratios, consent fees, thresholds

